{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox film | name = 7 Days in Syria | image = 7 Days in Syria.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Theatrical release poster | film name = | director = [[Robert Rippberger]] | producer = [[Janine di Giovanni]], [[Robert Rippberger]], Scott Rosenfelt, [[Matthew VanDyke]] | narrator = | starring = [[Janine di Giovanni]], Nicole Tung, [[Steven Sotloff]], James Foley | music = R. B. Music Group | cinematography = Patrick Wells, [[Matthew VanDyke]] | editing = Gabriel Cullen | studio = Aletheia Films, Cinema Vertitas | distributor = Ro*co Films, [[FilmBuff]], Gathr | released = {{Film date|2015}} | runtime = 75 minutes | country = United States | language = English, Arabic | budget = | gross = }}
'''''7 Days in Syria''''' is a 2015 American [[documentary film]] directed and produced by [[Robert Rippberger]]. Filmed in November 2012, it captures the human side of war and what life is like in Syria for the millions trying to escape. The film has played in over 50 cities worldwide (including Los Angeles, San Francisco, Washington D.C., New York, Toronto, London, Paris, Dublin, Norrkoping, Amsterdam, and Sydney),<ref>{{cite web|title=7 Days in Syria screenings|url=http://www.7daysinsyriafilm.com/screenings/|website=7 Days in Syria Official Site}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=7 DAYS IN SYRA SCREENING WITH JOURNALIST JANINE DI GIOVANNI|url=https://www.aup.edu/news-events/events/2016-04-11/7-days-syra-screening-journalist-janine-di-giovanni|website=The American University of Paris|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=di Giovanni|first1=Janine|title=Paris Is Mourning: One Journalist Reckons With Terror|url=http://www.vogue.com/13371069/paris-terrorist-attacks/|accessdate=25 October 2016|publisher=Vogue}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Gilbey|first1=Ryan|title=This week’s new film events|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/aug/28/this-weeks-new-film-events|accessdate=25 October 2016|publisher=The Guardian|date=28 August 2015}}</ref> on television in Denmark, Sweden, and China,<ref>{{cite web|title=7 Days in Syria Company Credits|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2634576/companycredits|website=IMDB|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref> to Angelina Jolie,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gandelman|first1=Joe|title=MOVIE REVIEW: "7 DAYS IN SYRIA" (A MUST VIEW FILM GIVEN RECENT DEVELOPMENTS)|url=http://themoderatevoice.com/210904/|accessdate=25 October 2016|agency=The Moderate Voice|issue=24 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ro*co Films|url=http://www.rocofilms.com/film.php?code=SYRA|website=7 Days in Syria|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref> to senior members of the [[United Nations]], and at Britain's [[House of Lords]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Staff|first1=AHT|title="7 Days in Syria" screening in British Parliament; House of Lords|url=http://ahtribune.com/world/north-africa-south-west-asia/38-syria-crisis/416-7-days-in-syria-house-of-lords.html|accessdate=25 October 2016|publisher=American Herald Tribune|date=23 January 2016}}</ref> The film was released internationally by Ro*co flims, throughout North America by [[FilmBuff]], by Gathr films for theatrical-on-demand, and online through Hulu.<ref>{{Citation|title=7 Days in Syria on Hulu|url=https://www.hulu.com/watch/1266130|accessdate=2018-05-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Gorman|first1=Michele|title=WATCH: TRAILER FOR '7 DAYS IN SYRIA,' A DOCUMENTARY ABOUT REPORTING ON WAR|url=http://www.newsweek.com/trailer-7-days-syria-janine-di-giovanni-396683|accessdate=25 October 2016|publisher=Newsweek|date=11 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=di Giovanni|first1=Janine|title=REPORTER DOCUMENTS LIFE IN ALEPPO IN '7 DAYS IN SYRIA'|url=http://www.newsweek.com/life-aleppo-7-days-syria-491850|accessdate=25 October 2016|publisher=Newsweek|date=21 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=7 Days in Syria|url=https://gathr.us/films/7-days-in-syria|website=Gathr|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Internationell stjärna till filmfestivalen|url=http://nt.se/kultur-noje/internationell-stjarna-till-filmfestivalen-12099306.aspx|accessdate=25 October 2016|publisher=Kultur Noje|date=7 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Interview with Robert Rippberger – producer/director of 7 Days in Syria.|url=http://www.fingalfilmfest.com/interview-with-robert-rippberger-producerdirector-of-7-days-in-syria/|accessdate=25 October 2016|agency=Fingal Film Festival|publisher=Newstalk 106-108FM|date=20 September 2015}}</ref>
==Synopsis== ''7 Days in Syria'' is a harrowing look at the human side of war and what so many refugees are escaping from within Syria. The film seeks out the heroes of Aleppo, chronicling the civilians keeping the city running, providing bread, administering medical supplies, burying dead bodies, and those internally documenting the atrocities for posterity and war tribunals. It's a war film unlike any other that also sheds light on the incredible distances journalists go to shine a light on some of the darkest places in the world.
==Reception==
===Critical response=== {{Quote|text=7 Days in Syria gives a window into the lives of families struggling to survive on the frontlines of the Syria conflict. Their courage and resilience shines through in impossible circumstances. |author=[[Angelina Jolie]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Films|first1=Ro*co|title=7 Days in Syria Trailer|url=https://vimeo.com/146315045|website=Vimeo|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref>}}
The "Moderate Voice" also gave it 5 stars writing:<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gandelman|first1=Joe|title=MOVIE REVIEW: "7 DAYS IN SYRIA" (A MUST VIEW FILM GIVEN RECENT DEVELOPMENTS)|url=http://themoderatevoice.com/210904/|accessdate=25 October 2016|agency=The Moderate Voice|issue=24 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ro*co Films|url=http://www.rocofilms.com/film.php?code=SYRA|website=7 Days in Syria|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref> {{Quote|text=If you could make a documentary required viewing, 7 Days in Syria would be it.}}
''DC FilmDom'' gave it 5 stars and wrote:<ref>{{cite news|last1=Parsons|first1=Michael|title=7 Days in Syria|url=http://www.dcfilmdom.com/2015/10/7-days-in-syria/|accessdate=25 October 2016|publisher=DC FilmDom|date=8 October 2015}}</ref> {{Quote|text=Beyond sobering, filmmaker Robert Rippberger’s snapshot of the ongoing Syrian Civil War brings the conflict unprecedented visibility via war journalist and Middle East specialist Janine di Giovanni.}}
On [[IMDB]], the film has a score of 8.3 out of 10 based on 139 ratings, with a median rating of 9 out of 10.<ref>{{cite web|title=7 Days in Syria Rating|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2634576/ratings|website=IMDB|accessdate=25 October 2016}}</ref>
