{{unreferenced|date=August 2008}} {{Infobox video game |title = Bun Fun |image = |caption= |developer = A. J. Turner |publisher = [[Squirrel]] |designer = |engine = |released = [[1983 in video gaming|1983]] |genre = [[Action video game|Action]] |modes = Single player |platforms = [[Acorn Electron]], [[BBC Micro]] }}
'''''Bun Fun''''' is a computer game written by A.J. Turner for the [[BBC Micro]] home computer and published by Squirrel Software on cassette in {{vgy|1983}}. It was later ported to the [[Acorn Electron]].
==Gameplay== In the game, the player manages a production line. A number of buns sit on a conveyor belt and, by rhythmic tapping of two keys on the computer, the player decorates them with icing, sugar and walnuts to produce a 'gudbun'. The more gudbuns the player produces, the more wages that player earns.
==External links== <!-- * [http://www.acornelectron.co.uk/profs/cats/squirrel.html#bunf Link to Bun Fun on Acorn Electron World] --> * [https://web.archive.org/web/20081216130736/http://www.acornelectron.co.uk:80/eug/revs/squirrel/r-bunf.html Review of Bun Fun by the Electron User Group]
