{{Use British English|date=July 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox company | name = Ivory Tower SASU | logo = Ubisoft Ivory Tower.png | logo_caption = Logo in use since 2018 | type = [[Subsidiary]] | industry = [[Video game industry]] | founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2007|09}} in [[Lyon]], France | founders = {{Unbulleted list|Ahmed Boukhelifa|Stéphane Beley|Emmanuel Oualid}} | key_people = {{Unbulleted list|Ahmed Boukhelifa|([[managing director]])|Stéphane Beley|([[creative director]])|Emmanuel Oualid|([[Chief financial officer|CFO]])}} | hq_location_city = [[Villeurbanne]] | hq_location_country = France | num_employees = 100 | num_employees_year = 2015 | parent = [[Ubisoft]] (2015–present) | website = {{URL|http://www.ivory-tower.fr/|ivory-tower.fr}} }}
'''Ivory Tower SASU''' is a French [[video game developer]] based in [[Villeurbanne]]. The company was founded by three ex-[[Eden Games]] employees in September 2007 and acquired by [[Ubisoft]] in October 2015. Ivory Tower is the developer of ''The Crew'' series, which comprises ''[[The Crew (video game)|The Crew]]'' (2014) and ''[[The Crew 2]]'' (2018).
== History == Ivory Tower was founded in [[Lyon]] in September 2007 by Ahmed Boukhelifa, Stéphane Beley and Emmanuel Oualid.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.edge-online.com/features/the-eden-project-why-the-crew-creator-ivory-tower-quit-test-drive-unlimited-2-to-start-all-over-again/ |title=The Eden project: why The Crew creator Ivory Tower quit Test Drive Unlimited 2 to start all over again |first=Neil |last=Long |date=27 November 2013 |website=[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131201005436/http://www.edge-online.com/features/the-eden-project-why-the-crew-creator-ivory-tower-quit-test-drive-unlimited-2-to-start-all-over-again/ |archivedate=1 December 2013 |deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2015/10/06/ubisoft-acquires-the-crew-developer-ivory-tower |title=Ubisoft Acquires The Crew Developer Ivory Tower |first=Luke |last=Reilly |date=5 October 2015 |website=ign.com |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> All three founders were previously employed by [[Eden Games]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mcvuk.com/development/ubisoft-acquires-ivory-tower |title=Ubisoft acquires Ivory Tower |author= |date= |website=mcvuk.com |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> Ivory Tower's first game, ''[[The Crew (video game)|The Crew]]'', was announced through its publisher, [[Ubisoft]], in June 2013,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vg247.com/2013/06/10/the-crew-announced-at-ubisoft-e3-presser/ |title=The Crew announced at Ubisoft E3 presser - VG247 |author= |date=10 June 2013 |website=vg247.com |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> and released for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox 360]] and [[Xbox One]] in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2014-10-06-the-crew-release-date-set-for-december |title=The Crew release date set for December |author= |date= |website=eurogamer.net |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> On 5 October 2015, as ''The Crew'' reached 3 million players, Ubisoft announced that they had acquired Ivory Tower for an undisclosed sum.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/the-crew-reaches-3-million-players-ubisoft-acquire/1100-6431160/ |title=The Crew Reaches 3 Million Players, Ubisoft Acquires Developer |first=Eddie |last=Makuch |date=5 October 2015 |website=gamespot.com |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2015-10-05-ubisoft-acquires-ivory-tower-studio |title=Ubisoft acquires Ivory Tower studio |author= |date= |website=gamesindustry.biz |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> At the time, the studio housed 100 employees.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2015-10-06-ubisoft-buys-the-crew-developer-ivory-tower |title=Ubisoft buys The Crew developer Ivory Tower |author= |date= |website=eurogamer.net |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> Ivory Tower's second game, ''[[The Crew 2]]'', was announced by Ubisoft in June 2017,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shacknews.com/article/100264/e3-2017-ubisoft-shows-off-the-crew-2 |title=E3 2017: Ubisoft Shows Off The Crew 2 |author= |date= |website=Shacknews |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref> and released for Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 4, Xbox One in June 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/the-crew-2-preview |title=The Crew 2 Once Again Erases My Home State From History |author= |date= |website=USgamer.net |accessdate=7 July 2018}}</ref>
== Games developed == {| class="wikitable sortable" ! Year ! Title ! Platform(s) |- | 2014 | ''[[The Crew (video game)|The Crew]]'' | [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]] |- | 2018 | ''[[The Crew 2]]'' | Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 4, Xbox One |}
