'''''Snoop Dogg's Father Hood''''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Reality television|reality]] [[television series]], executive produced and directed by [[David Roma]], as well as Ted Chung, Constance Schwartz and Anthony Mandler.<ref>{{cite web|title=Development Update: Week of July 16–20|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2007/07/20/development-update-week-of-july-16-20-25017/7428/|accessdate=3 December 2012}}</ref>  The series debuted on December 9, 2007 in the [[United States]] on [[E!]], with the second and final season premiering on November 30, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=E! Brings Families Together for Laughs Thanksgiving Weekend When the Second Season of "Snoop Dogg's Father Hood" Premieres Sunday, November 30th at 10:30 P.M., ET/PT|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2008/11/11/e-brings-families-together-for-laughs-thanksgiving-weekend-when-the-second-season-of-snoop-doggs-father-hood-premieres-sunday-november-30th-at-1030-pm-et-pt-29488/20081111e01/|accessdate=3 December 2012}}</ref>

==Premise==
The series follows the daily life of [[rapper]] [[Snoop Dogg]] and his family. His family includes his [[wife]] Shante, daughter Cori whom he calls "Choc", son Cordell whom he calls "Rook", and his oldest son Corde whom he calls "Spank".

